# Havanat Backend — Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values. The backend will warn on startup if any required variable is missing.

```env
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=4000

# Database (Postgres, e.g. Neon, Supabase, Vercel Postgres, or local)
DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/havanat

# JWT — generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=
JWT_ACCESS_TTL=1h
JWT_REFRESH_TTL=30d

# CORS — comma-separated list of allowed origins
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# Rate limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=120

# Object storage (S3-compatible) for product images, lookbook, proof-of-delivery, etc.
S3_BUCKET=
S3_REGION=
S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
S3_PUBLIC_BASE=

# Email (Resend)
RESEND_API_KEY=
EMAIL_FROM=orders@havanat.ng

# Payment providers
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=
FLUTTERWAVE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
```
